author: COMSOL
description: Power inductors are a central part of many low-frequency power applications. They are, for example, used in the switched power supply for the motherboard and all other components in a computer. This example shows how to use the Terminal boundary condition to extract the inductance. It also shows how to solve the model with and without gauge.
label: power_inductor.mph
